data.text:
Presentation on theme: "Married to Ekaterina Svanidze 18 December 1878 May 1940: Listen to My 5 year plans they will help us get out of this depression, were are behind the rest."— Presentation transcript:

1 Married to Ekaterina Svanidze 18 December 1878 May 1940: Listen to My 5 year plans they will help us get out of this depression, were are behind the rest of the world by so many years and we must work together to become number 1 April 1940: Meeting up with the president of the united states, hopefully we can make an agreement to take down Germany Mr. President: Ah, Yes Mr. Stalin I will make sure my secret service tends to your needs

2 The Germans will pay for invading Russia! Wall II July 1940:The French Shall help us in our War against the Germans 10235 people like this French Soldier: Bonjour Monsieur Stalin, we shall fight for you as we fight for our own leader! August 1942:The Germans will pay for invading Russia! Russian Soldier: I could not agree more! French Soldier: I agree we must defeat the Germans

3 I have Decided On collective farms as one of my 5 year plan Goals Wall III Russian Citizen: I Think these would help out our economy, it will create more jobs One More announcement ANY surplus crops you make, you are able to sell and keep the profits for your self Russian Farmer: Thank you, now I am able to afford new cloths and a nicer place for my family Peasant: Thank you Prime Minister it will give me a chance to make some money again

4 Ekaterina Svanidze: Can’t wait to see you again stalin your not as bad as they say Wall IV We shall destroy the germans for going against us! Just met a wonderful girl named Ekaterina Svanidze Nazi Soldier: Good Luck, Can’t wait to kill you

5 If the opposition disarms, all is well and good. If it refuses to disarm, we shall disarm our selves Wall V Russian Citizen: Well put Stalin! Russian Soldier: We Shall destroy our opposition Not Disarm THEM!!!

6 Male 18 December 1878 Gori, Tiflis Governorate, Maried to Ekaterina Svanidze Communist Party of the Soviet Union none Hanging out with the Bolsheviks Telling people what to do Classical Music The Soviet Network Chapaev Frankenstein I wish that I could just tell every one in the world what to do and they would listen… because if they don’t listen I might have to kill them. Profile

7 Friends Franklin Delano RooseveltMao ZedongEkaterina Svanidze Vyacheslav Molotov Leon Trotsky Osip Mandelstam Vladimir LeninNadezhda Alliluyeva Svetlana Alliluyeva Harry S Truman
